rComments: She is a very reasonable, caring and thoughtful professor. She is very respectful of her students and has a lot of passion for her field thus making you take the material and readings as seriously as she does. Really inspiring woman in the field of Anthropology.

The lectures were very  clear. The readings were somewhat heavy. The interpretation papers which make up a chunk of your grade seemed unrelated to the lectures and readings. Professor Patton was very understanding and helpful throughout the entire course.
